WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.777
Legal Frameworks


00:00:01.777 --> 00:00:02.761
1.


00:00:02.761 --> 00:00:06.437
HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act)**:


00:00:07.267 --> 00:00:11.769
A federal law that protects the privacy and security of patients' health information.


00:00:11.769 --> 00:00:15.531
It establishes standards for the handling of medical records, giving patients


00:00:15.531 --> 00:00:18.256
the right to access their information and understand how it is


00:00:18.256 --> 00:00:19.366
used.


00:00:19.366 --> 00:00:20.136
2.


00:00:20.136 --> 00:00:23.622
OSHA (Occupational Safety and Health Administration)**:


00:00:24.452 --> 00:00:28.814
A U.S. regulatory agency focused on ensuring safe working conditions.


00:00:28.814 --> 00:00:32.821
OSHA sets standards for workplace safety and requires employers to implement


00:00:32.821 --> 00:00:36.783
practices that protect employees from injury and illness, including in healthcare


00:00:36.783 --> 00:00:37.942
settings.


00:00:37.942 --> 00:00:38.892
3.


00:00:38.892 --> 00:00:40.424
Informed Consent**:


00:00:41.254 --> 00:00:48.471
A crucial healthcare principle requiring providers to inform patients about the risks, benefits, and alternatives of treatments.


00:00:48.471 --> 00:00:53.951
This process ensures patients can make informed decisions about their care and provide consent voluntarily.

